13:07.125 --> 13:08.208
You got to get the babies!

13:08.255 --> 13:09.220
Where are you going, hon?

13:09.289 --> 13:12.223
I... (SIGHS) I'm going to get Jasper.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.925
How are you gonna do that?

13:14.000 --> 13:16.250
(SIGHS) I know where he is.

13:16.296 --> 13:18.959
He's been living by the
prison, so I have to go get him.

13:18.984 --> 13:22.200
Wait, what? You knew where
Jasper was this whole time?

13:24.130 --> 13:25.095
I-I should go.

13:25.120 --> 13:26.616
No, we need to talk about this.

13:26.641 --> 13:28.592
But can't it wait? There's
a killer on the loose.

13:28.626 --> 13:29.709
He could be anywhere.

13:29.809 --> 13:32.877
(PIANO PLAYING TENSE MUSIC)

13:39.042 --> 13:41.918
(PLAYING OFF-KEY)

13:46.593 --> 13:48.593
(MUSIC STOPS)

13:49.509 --> 13:52.663
I'm back...

13:55.918 --> 13:57.710
- ♪ Bennie ♪
- (PLAYING OFF-KEY)

13:57.771 --> 13:59.804
♪ Bennie, Bennie ♪

13:59.873 --> 14:03.951
♪ Bennie, Bennie and the Jets. ♪

14:04.842 --> 14:06.559
KARL: Yeah, I got out, like, right away.

14:06.584 --> 14:07.864
It was so easy.

14:07.889 --> 14:10.815
Guess I was just so motivated to
get back here and see you guys.

14:10.884 --> 14:12.294
It's all I needed.

14:12.319 --> 14:14.386
It's a real testament to
setting goals. (CHUCKLES)

14:14.721 --> 14:17.555
Oh, well, what the hell we gonna do now?

14:17.624 --> 14:22.627
Look... I know the person
I want to be deep inside.

14:23.563 --> 14:26.072
But I also know who I am.

14:28.083 --> 14:30.250
And I'm just gonna keep coming back.

14:32.548 --> 14:34.926
You know what you need to do.

14:39.148 --> 14:41.047
So, how do we do this?

14:41.115 --> 14:44.350
Well, first of all, are
there any volunteers?

14:48.167 --> 14:51.542
Oh, sure. Everyone looks at
me when someone needs killing.

14:51.626 --> 14:53.267
No, I don't want to do it.

14:53.330 --> 14:56.056
I took the liberty of
cutting up some straws.

14:56.094 --> 14:59.345
Yeah, I guess drawing straws
is as fair as anything.

14:59.916 --> 15:01.732
You know how it works.

15:02.206 --> 15:04.172
Nobody can back out.

15:04.276 --> 15:05.909
Fair is fair.

15:07.497 --> 15:09.430
(SIGHS)

15:19.667 --> 15:21.585
You got to draw one, hon.

15:21.688 --> 15:24.489
I know. We are talking
about murdering someone,

15:24.557 --> 15:26.757
so... just give me a second.

15:36.959 --> 15:39.710
Okay, hold out your straws.

15:43.610 --> 15:44.809
Oh.

16:09.869 --> 16:11.936
TANDY: Hey, Care Bear.

16:12.005 --> 16:13.770
You okay?

16:15.067 --> 16:17.666
Yeah. I'm all bubbles and baubles.

16:17.667 --> 16:19.917
(CHUCKLES) Thanks for asking.

16:21.478 --> 16:23.399
You know I'm not gonna let you do it.

16:23.424 --> 16:25.516
Well, then who's gonna do it?

16:25.832 --> 16:27.932
- Me.
- No, Tandy.

16:27.957 --> 16:31.522
Fair is fair and I
drew the shortest straw.

16:32.501 --> 16:33.733
Did you?

16:37.626 --> 16:38.891
Tandy.

16:38.916 --> 16:40.440
You said it yourself.

16:40.465 --> 16:42.432
Fair is fair.

16:52.959 --> 16:56.543
You know I-I cut my straw, right?

16:56.959 --> 16:58.502
Yeah, I know.

16:58.551 --> 17:00.169
'Cause mine was one
of the longer straws.

17:00.194 --> 17:01.693
I mean, we all saw it.

17:02.887 --> 17:04.454
Thanks, Tandy.

17:04.557 --> 17:07.558
(CHUCKLES) I'm not doing
this for that, Carol. Okay?

17:07.627 --> 17:10.035
I already got more than
enough praise inside.

17:10.105 --> 17:11.796
I tried to cut it privately,

17:11.897 --> 17:14.531
but it ended up being
a rather public affair.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.310
Had to borrow scissors and, you know,

17:16.336 --> 17:17.935
cried a little bit and such.

17:18.574 --> 17:20.503
But yeah, you're welcome.

17:20.529 --> 17:23.762
This is, uh, gonna be very hard for me.

17:37.918 --> 17:39.168
You ready?

17:39.234 --> 17:41.934
Yeah, thanks for indulging me.

17:41.970 --> 17:43.961
Just put on some brown underwear,

17:43.986 --> 17:45.271
you know, obvious reasons.

17:45.306 --> 17:49.175
Of course. Uh, so I created
a little death area for you.

17:49.210 --> 17:51.344
So if you could, uh, please
just make your way over

17:51.375 --> 17:53.584
to this little coffin right here.

17:53.600 --> 17:55.669
I'd appreciate it.

17:57.218 --> 18:00.286
Hmm, interesting choice.

18:00.962 --> 18:02.729
You don't like it.

18:02.754 --> 18:04.090
No, no, no. I love it.

18:06.298 --> 18:09.332
Hey. I love it.

18:12.066 --> 18:13.684
Well, thank you.

18:13.709 --> 18:16.112
Look, the group wanted to be here,

18:16.148 --> 18:19.182
but they really didn't want to be here.

18:19.534 --> 18:21.567
Well, please tell them good-bye for me.

18:21.627 --> 18:24.187
Gals! Karl says good-bye!

18:24.212 --> 18:26.744
- CAROL: Bye, Karl!
- GAIL: So long, Karl!

18:26.792 --> 18:28.959
- MELISSA: See ya!
- Thank you!

18:29.406 --> 18:33.352
Well, uh, if you don't mind,
uh, this is very hard for me.

18:33.388 --> 18:37.451
So to separate myself from the
grim reality of the situation,

18:37.476 --> 18:41.452
I thought it'd be helpful to
do a, uh, a theme execution.

18:41.477 --> 18:42.395
Love it.

18:42.430 --> 18:43.680
Oh, good.

18:43.705 --> 18:45.932
Now, I've chosen the Broadway
smash,<i> Hamilton.</i>

18:45.967 --> 18:48.000
And obviously, I'll
be Alexander Hamilton

18:48.036 --> 18:49.268
and you will be Aaron Berg.

18:49.337 --> 18:51.170
- Burr.
- You need a sweater?

18:51.205 --> 18:52.827
- I'm fine.
- (CHUCKLES)

18:52.852 --> 18:55.374
I guess it's not gonna matter
in a few minutes anyway, huh?

18:55.443 --> 18:57.567
Well, this is it.

18:57.592 --> 19:00.212
So, uh, I'm gonna turn around,

19:00.452 --> 19:03.653
walk ten paces, and
then pull out the gun

19:03.678 --> 19:06.218
and shoot you in the face.

19:06.519 --> 19:10.056
Um, if it's okay, it would
help me take my mind off things

19:10.091 --> 19:11.924
if I could keep playing this.

19:11.960 --> 19:14.808
I know it's anachronistic for
the <i> Hamilton</i> time period,

19:14.833 --> 19:18.197
but so was rap and people
seemed to like that.

19:18.419 --> 19:21.154
Hey, cube it up.

19:22.329 --> 19:25.104
Practice shot, vase!

19:25.451 --> 19:27.921
Ah. Sucker moved on me.

19:27.946 --> 19:29.438
CAROL: Is it over?

19:29.463 --> 19:31.944
Practice shot! Doing it now!

19:31.980 --> 19:35.047
CAROL: Okay, uh, bye again, Karl!

19:35.116 --> 19:37.848
Bye! Who's that, Gail?

19:37.873 --> 19:39.251
Carol!

19:39.287 --> 19:40.686
Sorry.

19:40.711 --> 19:43.990
I'm gonna get your names right
if it's the last thing I do.

19:44.025 --> 19:45.291
(CHUCKLES) Oh.

19:45.326 --> 19:47.360
Which, I guess, you know...

19:47.699 --> 19:49.432
It begins.

20:04.334 --> 20:05.960
(EXHALES)

20:07.595 --> 20:09.348
One...

20:10.209 --> 20:12.001
two...

20:12.805 --> 20:13.632
three...

20:13.657 --> 20:15.868
- So I move this around here.
- Four...

20:15.893 --> 20:17.323
This will easily go in...

20:17.358 --> 20:20.259
- Five paces! Halfway there!
- Take your time.

20:20.294 --> 20:21.644
I'm almost finished with this cube.

20:21.667 --> 20:24.001
Six... seven...

20:24.032 --> 20:26.756
- Mm, almost there.
- Eight...

20:26.781 --> 20:28.394
nine...

20:32.058 --> 20:33.139
ten.

20:33.174 --> 20:35.777
Oh. Hello.

20:35.846 --> 20:37.902
Here we go.

20:38.446 --> 20:40.554
Ooh! Neato! (GASPS) Got it!

20:40.579 --> 20:42.212
I can't do...

20:55.209 --> 20:57.292
CAROL: Did you do it?

20:57.375 --> 21:00.500
Oh... he gone.

